  <title translate="true">Creating a package comment</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Creating a package comment</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">It is usual to include a comment with the package that explains what it is for and how to start using it. In order to do this select the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Comment</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab and type an appropriate comment in the pane at the bottom of the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Package Browser</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. You can save the comment by choosing </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Workspace /Accept</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or by typing </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Ctrl+S</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="PackageBrowser_Animals.png" scale="63.67%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
  </body>
</topic>
